                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#iiir(ecto)" facs="003">Fol. iiir(ecto)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1099StMary">St Mary</ref> stands before a crowd</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#74r" facs="077"> f. 74r,upper left</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref>,<persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">St George of Lydda</persName> and the <term key="dragon" ana="#dragon"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#74r" facs="077"> f. 74r, upper right</locus><desc>Jesus heals the paralytic man <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1074JesusHealsParalytic"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: AT1074JesusHealsParalytic</span></ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#74r" facs="077"> f. 74r, lower left</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1062CoronationMary">Coronation of Mary</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#74r" facs="077"> f. 74r, lower right</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1005Crucifixion">Crucifixion of Jesus</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6"><locus target="#74v" facs="078">Fol. 74v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1084JesusChrist">JesusChrist</ref>, with his disciples, before a crowd.  Jesus stretches out his arm to one man in the crowd</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7"><locus target="#75r" facs="078">Fol. 75r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1005Crucifixion">Crucifixion of Jesus</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8"><locus target="#75v" facs="079">Fol. 75v</locus><desc>A red box with two panels: upper is <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1030Trinity">The Trinity</ref> surrounded by the four living creatures; lower is two saints, with censers, in front of five <term key="angel" ana="#angel"/>s</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d9"><locus target="#79r" facs="082">Fol. 79r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1099StMary">St Mary</ref> stands in the space that would have been the third column of text</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d10"><locus target="#79v" facs="083">Fol. 79v</locus><desc>A red box with two panels: upper is <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1084JesusChrist">JesusChrist</ref> blessing the children; lower is a saint, center, carrying a child saint, with three saints to the right and two to the left</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d11"><locus target="#80r" facs="083">Fol. 80r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d12"><locus target="#80v" facs="084">Fol. 80v</locus><desc>A red box with two panels: upper is <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1099StMary">St Mary</ref> and two men stand in front of a crowd; lower is a man with a book kneeling, center, with several men behind him</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d13">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#1r" facs="004">fols. 1r, </locus> (matrix of black dots);
                    a line of alternating red and black dots serves as a section divider (e.g., <locus target="#8r #10v" facs="011 014">8r, 10v</locus>)
                    </decoNote>
