                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                      A rejected leaf from a twentieth-century Zǝmmare has been used as a spine cover (<locus target="#i #82" facs="001 085">folss. i, 82, </locus>). A small portion shows on the stub visible between front cover and <locus target="#ii" facs="002">ii, </locus>; two columns of text show on the portion showing between the back cover and the rest of the textblock. The fold lines and holes visible on <locus target="#82v" facs="086">82v</locus> indicate the sheet was used already once before in the same manner as a spine cover
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#iir(ecto)" facs="002">Fol. iir(ecto)</locus>
                    the title of the work is written
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#iiv(erso) #81r #81v" facs="003 084 085">Fols. iiv(erso), 81r, 81v</locus>
                    blank
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    <locus target="#1r" facs="004">Fol. 1r</locus>
                    The owner, Gäbrä Giyorgis
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#82v" facs="086">Fol. 82v</locus>
                    a list of types of Zǝmmare chants, written in pencil
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    marginal notation throughout, some of which may be overlooked text
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quires 2–5 and 8
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <desc>
                      Scribal intervention:
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#2v #7r #8v #13v" facs="006 010 012 017">folss. 2v, 7r, 8v, 13v, </locus>, etc.);
                      lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#23r" facs="026">23r, </locus>);
                      lines of text are written interlinearly with a symbol (┴) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#35r" facs="038"> f. 35r, col. 2, line 8</locus>;<locus target="#36r" facs="039"> f. 36r, col. 3, line 3</locus>), and in another case in the upper margin where the symbol (┴) is written in pencil (<locus target="#47r" facs="050"> f. 47r, col. 3, line 21</locus>);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#18r" facs="021">18r</locus>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
